---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="Developer, writer, builder. Here's a bit about me.">
  <article class="prose">
    <h1>About</h1>

    <p>
      Hey, I'm <strong>Your Name</strong> — a developer based in [Your City].
      I build [what you build] and write about what I learn along the way.
    </p>

    <p>
      I'm currently working on [current focus]. Before that, I [previous experience].
    </p>

    <h2>What I work with</h2>

    <p>
      My day-to-day stack includes TypeScript, React, Node.js, and whatever database
      makes sense for the problem. I care about developer experience, performance,
      and shipping things that actually work.
    </p>

    <h2>Why I write</h2>

    <p>
      Writing is how I solidify what I've learned. If something took me a week to figure out,
      I'd rather document it so you can figure it out in 10 minutes.
      I write about real problems I've hit — not textbook tutorials.
    </p>

    <h2>Get in touch</h2>

    <p>
      The best way to reach me is <a href="mailto:you@example.com">email</a>.
      You can also find me on <a href="https://github.com/yourusername" target="_blank" rel="noopener">GitHub</a>
      and <a href="https://twitter.com/yourusername" target="_blank" rel="noopener">X</a>.
    </p>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>
